Those sums are for the option that the driver chooses one lane, and doesn&#39;t change it until the end. Now, we can find the switch index, for options like starting at one road, and switching to the other. In this specific question I realized that the best point of switch between the arrays - is where the difference between the two collected sums until a certain index is the largest. In your example, it is index 6. That doesn&#39;t say that switching a lane is always giving a smaller sum.

    int roadIndex1 = road1.length-1;
